30:
Wow, there's tons of new smells
here! This is awesome!
35:
Hey, Lou! Remember rule number
one!
55:
My, my. Looks like we have our
hands full already.
59:
I knew I should've brought Nimbus
along!
63:
Guess I shouldn't be surprised, but
kids sure are a handful, huh!
66:
Indeed. You seem to be enjoying
yourself well enough, though.
71:
Well, you know how it is! Children
grow from making mistakes, and—
74:
Claw! Finny was asleep on the back
of that cart, and it just left!
78: Come on! Can't I catch a break?!
82:
What was I saying again? Ah, right.
Soushiro—
92:
Haha. You seem quite beset by
troubles, Claw.
96:
I've heard only vague details from
your world, though rumor has it
you've made quite an investment.
99:
It will be a while before they come
into their own, you know.
102:
Heh. I know, I know. Unlike burny
gloop, it's a while before you get a
return on investment with kids.
104: Actually, Suizen. The work we do? It's—
109:
Huh? It's Suizen! I didn't know you
were coming to play, too!
127: Lou! You gotta let him go—
132:
Shoot. He was our main sponsor for
this trip.
136: Do not worry. Izumi has a kind heart.
141:
Heh, yeah! Even someone like him
should play with kids his age
sometimes!
143:
By the way, Soushiro. How would you
have answered that question from
earlier?
146:
...Well, you were the one who was
asked.
149:
I'm much more interested in your
answer.
154:
The work we do? I think it's really all
we CAN do.
160:
The burny gloop? It's a miracle.
Normally, the problems we're
dealing with in my world are
impossible to do anything about.
162:
Trying to force change only makes
things worse. The peace we've
found between our peoples is no
different.
165:
But I can't forget that even in such a
tense situation, I can still be here for
these kids.
169:
This is the limit of what we can do, is
it? I... understand.
172:
Then allow me to help you today.
That's all I can do, right?
176:
I don't buy the humble act! But I'm in
your debt, Soushiro.
189:
Those two beat up some bandit kids
and yokai in the mountains, and
now they're leading them while
saying something about
reconciliation!
194: Just give me a break, already!
